dict.string: Blade jumps up during the cut
Blade does not stay down, even before cut
Cutter Assembly Binding
Blade engages properly, might be a dull blade.
Media is too thick, unable to cut
Left Hand Maintenance Panel not seated properly
Cutter might not be in locked position

Solution: Replace Blade

Step 1: Remove blade from Sheet Cutter Assembly.
            Check condition of blade

Step 2: If dull or damaged, replace the cutter blade

Step 3: Replace blade if dull or damaged
Down motion of blade is not smooth, blade may have a burr
Down motion of blade is not smooth, blade may have a burr

Solution: Remove and replace blade or blade holder

Step 1: There may be a burr or nick in the blade
            causing it to bind in the assembly. 

Step 2: If this is the case, remove the blade and replace it
Cutter blade is extended out too far
Cutter Carriage assembly is tilted, Might not be parallel to platen

Solution: Adjust blade depth

Step 1: Adjust the extension of the blade using the threaded
            cap on the blade holder

Step 2: Turn the adjustment cap counterclockwise
            to decrease the depth.
